e Rating}})}{113}}+({\mbox{course rating}}-{\mbox{par}})}"></span></dd></dl=
>
<p>The WHS contains measures to reduce a handicap index more quickly in the=
 case of exceptional scoring, and also to prevent a handicap index from ris=
ing too quickly. This is done by means of "soft" and "hard" caps based on t=
he lowest index during the previous 365 days; the soft cap reduces increase=
s above 3.0 to 50%, and the hard cap limits increases to 5.0. Updates to a =
golfer's handicap index are issued daily.
</p><p>Many elements of WHS have flexibility which allows for local authori=
ties to determine their own settings, but the basic handicap index calculat=
ion remains the same. Examples include: 9-hole scores may be scaled-up rath=
er than combined; <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline">=
<span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"displa=
y: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle ({\mbox{course rating}}-{\mbox{par}})}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mstyle displaystyle=3D"false" scriptlevel=3D"0">
            <mtext>course rating</mtext>
          </mstyle>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mstyle displaystyle=3D"false" scriptlevel=3D"0">
            <mtext>par</mtext>
          </mstyle>
        </mrow>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle ({\mbox{cours=
e rating}}-{\mbox{par}})}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/a9f0c2b14d210a62cb0d62c63a7f37db211ad297" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.838ex; width:21.025ex; height:2.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle ({=
\mbox{course rating}}-{\mbox{par}})}"></span> may be omitted from the cours=
e handicap calculation; and the rounded course handicap may be used in the =
playing handicap calculation.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-whscongu_22-0" class=3D"re=
ference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Handicap_(golf)#cite_note=
-whscongu-22"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>22<span class=3D"cite-br=
acket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"USGA_Handicap_System">USGA =
Handicap System</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editse=
ction-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?titl=
e=3DHandicap_(golf)&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D15" title=3D"Edit secti=
on: USGA Handicap System"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsectio=
n-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The first handicap system to be introduced by the USGA was largely the w=
ork of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DLeighton_Cal=
kins&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;redlink=3D1" class=3D"new" title=3D"Leighton Cal=
kins (page does not exist)">Leighton Calkins</a>, who based it on the Briti=
sh "three-score average" system where the handicap was calculated as the av=
erage of the best three scores to par in the last year. The key difference =
was the introduction of a par rating (later known as course rating), which =
was based on the ability of leading amateur <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Jerome_Travers" title=3D"Jerome Travers">Jerome Travers</a>, to a=
ccount for variances in the playing difficulty of different courses. After =
initially allowing clubs to determine their own ratings, at the behest of C=
alkins the USGA quickly began assigning ratings centrally. Course ratings w=
ere rounded to the nearest whole number until 1967, when they started being=
 given to one decimal place.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-usgahistory3_11-1" class=3D=
"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Handicap_(golf)#cite_n=
ote-usgahistory3-11"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>11<span class=3D"=
cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>In 1947, the number of scores used to calculate handicaps was increa=
sed to the best 10 from all scores ever recorded subject to a minimum of 50=
. However this was not uniformly implemented, with regional associations di=
sagreeing on the total number of rounds to be considered. In 1958, the USGA=
 specified that the best 10 from 25 scores would be used. This was reduced =
to 10 from 20 in 1967, which remains to this day although a further adjustm=
ent was made with the introduction of a "Bonus of Excellence" multiplier to=
 equalize handicaps and give better players a marginal advantage. Originall=
y 85%, the multiplier was changed to 96% after being seen to favor better p=
layers too heavily. In 1974, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Handi=
cap_(golf)#Maximum_hole_score">Equitable Stroke Control</a> was adopted in =
order to eliminate the effect of very high individual hole scores on handic=
ap calculations.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-usgahistory3_11-2" class=3D"reference">=
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Handicap_(golf)#cite_note-usgahist=
ory3-11"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>11<span class=3D"cite-bracket=
">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>With the system still not accounting for variances in playing diffic=
ulty for golfers of different abilities, in 1979 the USGA set to work on ho=
w to address the issue with the creation of the Handicap Research Team. The=
 result of their work was the creation of what is now the <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Slope_rating" title=3D"Slope rating">Slope system</=
a>. Slope was gradually introduced, firstly in Colorado in 1982, before bei=
ng implemented nationally from 1987. The USGA then set about making further=
 refinements to the course rating system, which at the time was still large=
ly dependent on length, to take account of many other factors affecting sco=
ring ability for a scratch golfer.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-usgahistory4_12-1" cl=
ass=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Handicap_(golf)#=
cite_note-usgahistory4-12"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>12<span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The USGA Course and Slope Rating sys=
tem is now used by most of the world's major handicapping systems.<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-whsqa2018_20-2" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Handicap_(golf)#cite_note-whsqa2018-20"><span class=3D"cite-=
bracket">[</span>20<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>The USGA Handicap System is used throughout the jurisdiction of the =
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/USGA" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=
=3D"USGA">USGA</a> (i.e. the United States and Mexico), and is also license=
d for use in many other countries around the world, e.g. <a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Golf_Canada" title=3D"Golf Canada">Canada</a>.<sup i=
d=3D"cite_ref-23" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Handicap_(golf)#cite_note-23"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>23<s=
pan class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The USGA has often resorted t=
o the courts to protect the integrity of its handicap system.  In one such =
case, the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/California_Courts_of_App=
eal" title=3D"California Courts of Appeal">California Court of Appeal</a> (=
First District) summarized the system's history:
</p>
<blockquote class=3D"templatequote"><p>The USGA was founded in 1894. One of=
 its chief contributions to the game of golf in the United States has been =
its development and maintenance since 1911 of the USGA handicap system&nbsp=
;... designed to enable individual golf players of different abilities to c=
ompete fairly with one another. Because permitting individual golfers to is=
sue their handicaps to themselves would inevitably lead to inequities and a=
buse, the peer review provided by authorized golf clubs and associations ha=
s always been an essential part of the [system]. Therefore, to protect the =
integrity and credibility of its [handicap system], the USGA has consistent=
ly followed a policy of only permitting authorized golf associations and cl=
ubs to issue USGA handicaps&nbsp;... In 1979, USGA assembled a handicap res=
earch team to investigate widespread criticisms of USGA's then-existing han=
dicap formula. The research team invested approximately a decade and up to =
$2 million conducting intensive analysis and evaluation of the various fact=
ors involved in developing a more accurate and satisfactory [system]. As a =
result, the research team developed new handicap formulas&nbsp;... designed=
 to measure the overall difficulty of golf courses, compare individual golf=
ers with other golfers of all abilities, take account of differences betwee=
n tournament and casual play, and adjust aberrant scores on individual hole=
s. USGA subsequently adopted and implemented these new [f]ormulas between 1=
987 and 1993.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-24" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Handicap_(golf)#cite_note-24"><span class=3D"cite-br=
acket">[</span>24<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup></p></block=
quote>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"USGA_Handicap_System_overvi=
ew">USGA Handicap System overview</h4><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span =
class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/w/index.php?title=3DHandicap_(golf)&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D16" t=
itle=3D"Edit section: USGA Handicap System overview"><span>edit</span></a><=
span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>A USGA handicap is calculated with a specific arithmetic formula that ap=
proximates how many strokes above or below <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Par_(score)" title=3D"Par (score)">par</a> a player might be able =
to play, based on the ten best scores of their last twenty rounds.<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-25" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Handicap_(golf)#cite_note-25"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>25<sp=
an class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>  The calculation has several v=
ariables:  the player's scores from their most recent rounds, and the cours=
e and slope ratings from those rounds.
</p><p>A <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Handicap_(golf)#Handicap_=
Differential">handicap differential</a> is calculated from each of the scor=
es after <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Equitable_Stroke_Control"=
 title=3D"Equitable Stroke Control">Equitable Stroke Control</a> (ESC), an =
adjustment which allows for a maximum number of strokes per hole based on t=
he player's course handicap, has been applied using the following formula:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e {\mbox{Handicap differential}}=3D{\frac {({\mbox{ESC adjusted score}}-{\m=
box{course rating}})\times {\mbox{113}}}{\mbox{slope rating}}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mstyle displaystyle=3D"false" scriptlevel=3D"0">
            <mtext>Handicap differential</mtext>
          </mstyle>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mstyle displaystyle=3D"false" scriptlevel=3D"0">
                  <mtext>ESC adjusted score</mtext>
                </mstyle>
              </mrow>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mstyle displaystyle=3D"false" scriptlevel=3D"0">
                  <mtext>course rating</mtext>
                </mstyle>
              </mrow>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
              <mo>=C3=97<!-- =C3=97 --></mo>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mstyle displaystyle=3D"false" scriptlevel=3D"0">
                  <mtext>113</mtext>
                </mstyle>
              </mrow>
            </mrow>
            <mstyle displaystyle=3D"false" scriptlevel=3D"0">
              <mtext>slope rating</mtext>
            </mstyle>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\mbox{Handic=
ap differential}}=3D{\frac {({\mbox{ESC adjusted score}}-{\mbox{course rati=
ng}})\times {\mbox{113}}}{\mbox{slope rating}}}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/af3e087efaf0c08b5a84613333120c728a7b6301" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -2.338ex; width:68.494ex; height:6.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle {\=
mbox{Handicap differential}}=3D{\frac {({\mbox{ESC adjusted score}}-{\mbox{=
course rating}})\times {\mbox{113}}}{\mbox{slope rating}}}}"></span></dd></=
dl>
<p>The handicap differentials are rounded to one decimal place, and the bes=
t 10 from the last 20 submitted scores are then averaged, before being mult=
iplied by 0.96 (the "bonus of excellence") and truncated to one decimal pla=
ce to produce the handicap index. Initial handicaps are calculated from a m=
inimum of five scores using ESC adjustments based on the course handicap co=
rresponding to a handicap index of 36.4 for men or 40.4 for women. If there=
 are at least 5 but fewer than 20 qualifying scores available, the handicap=
 index is calculated using a set number or differentials according to how m=
any scores are available.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-usgamanual_26-0" class=3D"refe=
rence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Handicap_(golf)#cite_note-u=
sgamanual-26"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>26<span class=3D"cite-br=
acket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<table class=3D"wikitable" style=3D"float: center;">
<tbody><tr>
<th>Number of rounds</th>
<th>Differentials to use
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td align=3D"center">5 or 6</td>
<td align=3D"center">lowest 1
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td align=3D"center">7 or 8</td>
<td align=3D"center">lowest 2
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td align=3D"center">9 or 10</td>
<td align=3D"center">lowest 3
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td align=3D"center">11 or 12</td>
<td align=3D"center">lowest 4
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td align=3D"center">13 or 14</td>
<td align=3D"center">lowest 5
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td align=3D"center">15 or 16</td>
<td align=3D"center">lowest 6
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td align=3D"center">17</td>
<td align=3D"center">lowest 7
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td align=3D"center">18</td>
<td align=3D"center">lowest 8
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td align=3D"center">19</td>
<td align=3D"center">lowest 9
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<p>The basic formula for calculating the handicap index is as follows (wher=
e <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"m=
we-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math =
xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle n}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>n</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle n}</annotatio=
n>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/a601995d55609f2d9f5e233e36fbe9ea26011b3b" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.338ex; width:1.395ex; height:1.676ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle n}"=
></span> is the number of differentials to use), with the result truncated =
to one decimal place:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e {\mbox{Handicap index}}=3D{\frac {0.96}{n}}\sum _{x=3D1}^{n}{\mbox{Differ=
ential}}_{x}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mstyle displaystyle=3D"false" scriptlevel=3D"0">
            <mtext>Handicap index</mtext>
          </mstyle>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>0.96</mn>
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <munderover>
          <mo>=E2=88=91<!-- =E2=88=91 --></mo>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>x</mi>
            <mo>=3D</mo>
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </munderover>
        <msub>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mstyle displaystyle=3D"false" scriptlevel=3D"0">
              <mtext>Differential</mtext>
            </mstyle>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>x</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\mbox{Handic=
ap index}}=3D{\frac {0.96}{n}}\sum _{x=3D1}^{n}{\mbox{Differential}}_{x}}</=
annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/f8d5b838ed8d7f65bda227958ce939db322fcaf7" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -3.005ex; width:40.544ex; height:6.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle {\=
mbox{Handicap index}}=3D{\frac {0.96}{n}}\sum _{x=3D1}^{n}{\mbox{Differenti=
al}}_{x}}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>The handicap index is not used directly for playing purposes, but used t=
o calculate a course handicap according to the slope rating of the set of t=
ees being used. The result is rounded to the nearest whole number.<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-GDusga_3-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Handicap_(golf)#cite_note-GDusga-3"><span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>[</span>3<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e {\mbox{Course Handicap}}=3D{\frac {({\mbox{Handicap index}}\times {\mbox{=
Slope Rating}})}{113}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mstyle displaystyle=3D"false" scriptlevel=3D"0">
            <mtext>Course Handicap</mtext>
          </mstyle>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mstyle displaystyle=3D"false" scriptlevel=3D"0">
                  <mtext>Handicap index</mtext>
                </mstyle>
              </mrow>
              <mo>=C3=97<!-- =C3=97 --></mo>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mstyle displaystyle=3D"false" scriptlevel=3D"0">
                  <mtext>Slope Rating</mtext>
                </mstyle>
              </mrow>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
            </mrow>
            <mn>113</mn>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\mbox{Course=
 Handicap}}=3D{\frac {({\mbox{Handicap index}}\times {\mbox{Slope Rating}})=
}{113}}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/8a915ad1afc304dfa2de224011316ba48b77cc75" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -1.838ex; width:54.367ex; height:5.676ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle {\=
mbox{Course Handicap}}=3D{\frac {({\mbox{Handicap index}}\times {\mbox{Slop=
e Rating}})}{113}}}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>Updates to a golfer's handicap index are issued periodically, generally =
once or twice per month depending on the local state and regional golf asso=
ciations.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-whsqa2018_20-3" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Handicap_(golf)#cite_note-whsqa2018-20"><spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>20<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a=
></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"CONGU_Unified_Handicapping_=
System">CONGU Unified Handicapping System</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection=
"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DHandicap_(golf)&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=
=3D17" title=3D"Edit section: CONGU Unified Handicapping System"><span>edit=
</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Following a meeting of the four men's golf unions of Great Britain and I=
reland in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/York" title=3D"York">Yor=
k</a> arranged by <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Royal_and_An=
cient_Golf_Club_of_St_Andrews" title=3D"The Royal and Ancient Golf Club of =
St Andrews">The Royal and Ancient Golf Club of St Andrews</a> in 1924, the =
British Golf Unions Joint Advisory Committee (later <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Council_of_National_Golf_Unions" title=3D"Council of Nati=
onal Golf Unions">Council of National Golf Unions</a>) was formed. The orga=
nization was tasked with creating a handicapping system that would be equit=
able to golfers of varying ability, and as a result the <b>Standard Scratch=
 Score and Handicapping Scheme</b> was devised. The system was introduced i=
n 1926, and used a "scratch score" system to rate courses, taking account t=
hat courses may play easier or more difficult than <a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Par_(golf)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Par (golf)">par=
</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-conguhistory_9-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Handicap_(golf)#cite_note-conguhistory-9"><spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>9<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a>=
</sup>
</p><p>A new system was introduced in 1983, which incorporated features of =
the Australian system. This was further revised in 1989 with the introducti=
on of the <i>Competition Scratch Score</i> (CSS), an adjustment to the <i>S=
tandard Scratch Score</i> (SSS), to take account of variances in course con=
ditions (setup, weather, etc.) on a given day.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-TGcongu_2=
-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Handicap_(=
golf)#cite_note-TGcongu-2"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>2<span clas=
s=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Further significant changes came in 1=
993 (buffer zones) and 1997 (Stableford Points Adjustment). In 2002, the Co=
uncil of National Golf Unions (CONGU) and the <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Ladies%27_Golf_Union" title=3D"Ladies' Golf Union">Ladies' Golf=
 Union</a> (LGU) began working together (the LGU had adopted a system simil=
ar to that of CONGU in 1998) and in February 2004 the <b>Unified Handicappi=
ng System</b> (UHS) came into force.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-conguhistory_9-2" c=
lass=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Handicap_(golf)=
#cite_note-conguhistory-9"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>9<span clas=
s=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>The Unified Handicapping System is used to manage handicaps for both=
 men and women who are members of affiliated <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Golf_club_(institution)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Golf clu=
b (institution)">golf clubs</a> in the United Kingdom and the Republic of I=
reland. The system is published by CONGU and administered by each of the in=
dividual unions on behalf of their members,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-GMcongu_27-0=
" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Handicap_(go=
lf)#cite_note-GMcongu-27"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>27<span clas=
s=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> with handicaps being managed locally =
by someone at each club; this person normally holds the position of competi=
tions or handicap secretary.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Unified_Handicapping_System=
_overview">Unified Handicapping System overview</h4><span class=3D"mw-edits=
ection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DHandicap_(golf)&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;s=
ection=3D18" title=3D"Edit section: Unified Handicapping System overview"><=
span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span><=
/div>
<p>Under the Unified Handicapping System, initial handicaps are allocated b=
ased on returned scores from 54 holes, usually three 18-hole rounds.<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-GMcongu_27-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Handicap_(golf)#cite_note-GMcongu-27"><span class=3D"cite-brac=
ket">[</span>27<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The number o=
f strokes taken on each hole is adjusted to maximum of double the par of th=
e hole before adding up the scores; adjustments were previously 2 over par =
for men and 3 over par for women.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-uhsmanual2016_28-0" cl=
ass=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Handicap_(golf)#=
cite_note-uhsmanual2016-28"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>28<span cl=
ass=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The best of the "adjusted gross dif=
ferentials" (AGD) between the adjusted score and the Standard Scratch Score=
 (SSS) is taken to calculate the initial handicap using the following formu=
la, with the result truncated to give a whole number:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e {\mbox{Initial handicap}}=3D{\frac {({\mbox{Lowest AGD}}+({\mbox{Lowest A=
GD}}\times {\mbox{0.13}}))}{\mbox{1.237}}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
