<p>In addition to playing in qualifying competitions, golfers in Category 2=
 and above may also submit a number of <i>extra day scores</i> in order to =
maintain their handicap. Handicaps are also reviewed annually and any neces=
sary adjustments made.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-ega_31-1" class=3D"reference"><a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Handicap_(golf)#cite_note-ega-31"><sp=
an class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>31<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></=
a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Golf_Australia_Handicap_Sys=
tem">Golf Australia Handicap System</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><spa=
n class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/w/index.php?title=3DHandicap_(golf)&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D21"=
 title=3D"Edit section: Golf Australia Handicap System"><span>edit</span></=
a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The Golf Australia Handicap System is maintained on GOLF Link, which was=
 a world-first computerized handicapping system developed by <a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Golf_Australia" title=3D"Golf Australia">Golf Au=
stralia</a>'s predecessor, the Australian Golf Union (AGU) in the 1990s. Wh=
en GOLF Link was first introduced it contained two key characteristics that=
 set it apart from other world handicapping systems at the time:
</p>
<ol><li>It used a Calculated Course Rating (CCR) to determine how difficult=
 the course was on the day, and upon which handicap adjustment was made.</l=
i>
<li>It utilized a 'swipe' card that enabled a player to access their handic=
ap from any GOLF Link terminal in Australia.</li></ol>
<p>In April 2010 GA adopted the USGA calculation method using the average o=
f the best 10 differentials of the player's past 20 total rounds, multiplie=
d by 0.96. In September 2011 this was altered to the best 8 out of 20 round=
s, multiplied by 0.93. The reasons for these changes were cited to restore =
equity between high and low handicaps. An =E2=80=98anchor' so that handicap=
s could not increase by more than 5 in a rolling 12-month period, <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Slope_rating" title=3D"Slope rating">slop=
e ratings</a>, and a more sophisticated version of CCR called the Daily Scr=
atch Rating (DSR) were implemented on January 23, 2014.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-=
gahandicap_33-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Handicap_(golf)#cite_note-gahandicap-33"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[<=
/span>33<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-=
NewGA_34-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ha=
ndicap_(golf)#cite_note-NewGA-34"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>34<s=
pan class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-35" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Handicap_(golf)#cit=
e_note-35"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>35<span class=3D"cite-brack=
et">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"GA_Handicap_System_overview=
">GA Handicap System overview</h4><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span clas=
s=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/=
index.php?title=3DHandicap_(golf)&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D22" title=
=3D"Edit section: GA Handicap System overview"><span>edit</span></a><span c=
lass=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The GA Handicap System is based on the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Stableford" title=3D"Stableford">Stableford</a> scoring system, and=
 uses slope and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Handicap_(golf)#Co=
urse_Rating">course rating</a> (called "Scratch Rating"). For handicapping =
purposes, the scratch rating is adjusted to reflect scoring conditions ("Da=
ily Scratch Rating"), and all scores are converted into Stableford points, =
called the Stableford Handicap Adjustment (SHA) and inherently applying <a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Handicap_(golf)#Maximum_hole_score">n=
et double bogey</a> adjustments, regardless of the scoring system being use=
d while playing.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-gahandicap_33-1" class=3D"reference"><a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Handicap_(golf)#cite_note-gahandicap=
-33"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>33<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]<=
/span></a></sup>
</p><p>Handicaps are calculated from the best 8 adjusted <a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Handicap_(golf)#Handicap_differential">differentials=
</a>, called "sloped played to" results, from the most recent 20 scores. Sh=
ould there be 3 or more but fewer than 20 scores available, a specified num=
ber of "sloped played to" results are used, per the table below.<sup id=3D"=
cite_ref-ausopen_36-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Handicap_(golf)#cite_note-ausopen-36"><span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>[</span>36<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<table class=3D"wikitable" style=3D"float: center;">
<tbody><tr>
