<p>The GA handicap is used to create a "<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Handicap_(golf)#Playing_or_course_handicap">daily handicap</a>", spec=
ific to the course and set of tees being used, using the following formula =
with the result rounded to the nearest whole number:<sup id=3D"cite_ref-aus=
open_36-3" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Han=
dicap_(golf)#cite_note-ausopen-36"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>36<=
span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e {\mbox{Daily handicap}}=3D{\frac {{\mbox{GA handicap}}\times {\mbox{Slope=
 Rating}}}{\mbox{113}}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
