<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"South_African_Handicap_Syst=
em">South African Handicap System</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span =
class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/w/index.php?title=3DHandicap_(golf)&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D23" t=
itle=3D"Edit section: South African Handicap System"><span>edit</span></a><=
span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Before 2018, the South African Handicap System used a proprietary course=
 rating system without slope, called Standard Rating, which included specif=
ic calculations for length and altitude. Handicaps were calculated using th=
e best 10 from the last 20 differentials, with differentials derived by mea=
ns of a simple (Standard Rating =E2=88=92 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Equitable_Stroke_Control" title=3D"Equitable Stroke Control">Adjust=
ed Gross</a>) formula. The system previously calculated handicaps against a=
n adjusted Standard Rating (called Calculated Rating) but this was suspende=
d in 2012.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-37" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Handicap_(golf)#cite_note-37"><span class=3D"cite-brack=
et">[</span>37<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Playing handi=
caps were simply the exact handicap, rounded to the nearest whole number.<s=
up id=3D"cite_ref-38" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Handicap_(golf)#cite_note-38"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>=
38<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>In September 2018, the renamed GolfRSA Handicap System adopted the U=
SGA Course and Slope Rating system. This necessitated a few additional chan=
ges (e.g. playing handicap and differential calculations), but the system r=
etained all other features (e.g. Adjusted Gross and no daily course rating =
adjustment). The playing handicap under the GolfRSA system includes the dif=
ference between the Course Rating and Par.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-39" class=3D"=
reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Handicap_(golf)#cite_no=
te-39"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>39<span class=3D"cite-bracket">=
]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>In October 2019, further changes were made which brought the GolfRSA=
 Handicap System further into line with the upcoming World Handicap System.=
 The changes introduced included reducing the number of differentials used =
in handicap calculations from 10 down to 8, net double bogey as the maximum=
 score per hole, reducing the minimum number of valid 18-hole scores requir=
ed for handicapping to three, and exceptional scoring reductions.<sup id=3D=
"cite_ref-40" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Handicap_(golf)#cite_note-40"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>40<span =
class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Argentinian_Handicap_System=
">Argentinian Handicap System</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span clas=
s=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/=
index.php?title=3DHandicap_(golf)&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D24" title=
=3D"Edit section: Argentinian Handicap System"><span>edit</span></a><span c=
lass=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The Argentine Golf Association (AAG) handicapping system is a relatively=
 simple one, using only a course rating, without slope. New handicaps requi=
re the submission of scorecards from five 18-hole rounds (or ten 9-hole rou=
nds). An initial handicap of 25 is normally used as a starting point, which=
 is then adjusted based on the submitted scores. Handicaps are updated once=
 every month, with current handicaps generated from a lookup table using th=
e average of the best eight differentials from the last 16 rounds. Golfers =
simply use their exact handicap for playing purposes.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-wh=
sqa2018_20-4" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Handicap_(golf)#cite_note-whsqa2018-20"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</spa=
n>20<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-41" =
class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Handicap_(golf=
)#cite_note-41"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>41<span class=3D"cite-=
bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Other_systems">Other system=
s</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket"=
>[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DHandicap_(=
golf)&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D25" title=3D"Edit section: Other syst=
ems"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></=
span></div>
<p>For the handicapping of golfers who are ineligible for an official handi=
cap, some system options are available:
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Peoria_System">Peoria Syste=
m</h4><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket"=
>[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DHandicap_(=
golf)&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D26" title=3D"Edit section: Peoria Sys=
tem"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></=
span></div>
<p>The <i>Peoria System</i><sup id=3D"cite_ref-42" class=3D"reference"><a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Handicap_(golf)#cite_note-42"><span cl=
ass=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>42<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></s=
up> was designed for the handicapping of all players competing in an event =
such as a <i>charity</i> or <i>corporate</i> golf day. Before play commence=
s, the organisers secretly select 6 holes (in readiness for handicapping pu=
rposes later) from the course to be played. When players have completed the=
ir rounds, they apply the <i>Peoria</i> algorithm to their scores on the se=
lected holes to determine their handicap for that round. They then subtract=
 that handicap from their gross score to give their net score - and the win=
ner is determined in the usual way.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-usgaunhandicapped_43=
-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Handicap_(=
golf)#cite_note-usgaunhandicapped-43"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>=
43<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Callaway_System">Callaway S=
ystem</h4><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-brac=
ket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DHandic=
ap_(golf)&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D27" title=3D"Edit section: Callaw=
ay System"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</s=
pan></span></div>
<p>The <i>Callaway System</i><sup id=3D"cite_ref-44" class=3D"reference"><a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Handicap_(golf)#cite_note-44"><span =
class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>44<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a><=
/sup> was designed with the same objective as <i>Peoria</i>. The <i>Callawa=
y</i> handicapping algorithm works by totaling a variable number of "worst"=
 scores achieved (subject to a double-par limit) according to a simple tabl=
e. A couple of adjustments are then made to this total to give the player's=
 handicap, which is then applied to their gross score as normal.<sup id=3D"=
cite_ref-usgaunhandicapped_43-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/Handicap_(golf)#cite_note-usgaunhandicapped-43"><span cl=
ass=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>43<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></s=
up>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Scheid_System">Scheid Syste=
m</h4><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket"=
>[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DHandicap_(=
golf)&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D28" title=3D"Edit section: Scheid Sys=
tem"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></=
span></div>
<p>The <i>Scheid System</i><sup id=3D"cite_ref-45" class=3D"reference"><a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Handicap_(golf)#cite_note-45"><span cl=
ass=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>45<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></s=
up> is similar to the Callaway System, except a different version of the ta=
ble is used.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-usgaunhandicapped_43-2" class=3D"reference"=
><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Handicap_(golf)#cite_note-usgaunh=
andicapped-43"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>43<span class=3D"cite-b=
racket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"System_36">System 36</h4><s=
pan class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span=
><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DHandicap_(golf)&am=
p;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D29" title=3D"Edit section: System 36"><span>e=
dit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p><i>System 36</i><sup id=3D"cite_ref-46" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Handicap_(golf)#cite_note-46"><span class=3D"c=
ite-bracket">[</span>46<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> is a=
 same-day handicapping system similar in function to <i>Callaway System</i>=
 and <i>Peoria System</i>. Throughout the round, the golfer accrues points =
based on the following formula:
</p>
<ul><li>Double bogey or worse: 0 points</li>
<li>Bogey: 1 point</li>
<li>Par or better: 2 points</li></ul>
<p>At the end of the round, points earned are tallied. The total is subtrac=
ted from 36, and the resulting number is the golfer's handicap allowance. T=
he golfer's net score can then be computed using their System 36 handicap a=
llowance.
</p>
